<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860F6B29FEFE8BC3FBFBF796" blockId="29.[241,1227,1878,2682]" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">
Type locality. 
<quantity id="4CBA9B30860F6B29FDE38BC3FD33F845" box="[571,681,1975,2014]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" unit="m" value="150.0">150 m</quantity>
west of 'Marohn' homestead, 
<quantity id="4CBA9B30860F6B29FF2D8B92FECEF796" box="[245,340,2022,2061]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" unit="km" value="4.0">4 km</quantity>
south-west of Gundy, NSW (Locality 28).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860F6B29FEFD846CFCF2F7F6" blockId="29.[241,1227,1878,2682]" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">Stratigraphic position. In biociastic limestone, upper part of the Dangarfield Formation.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860F6B29FEFD840CFBD4F73A" blockId="29.[241,1227,1878,2682]" box="[293,1102,2168,2209]" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">
Geographic distribution. 
<typeStatus id="54F98877860F6B29FD25840CFCC9F73A" box="[765,851,2168,2209]" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">Type</typeStatus>
locality only.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860F6B29FEFD84DFFC10F748" blockId="29.[241,1227,1878,2682]" box="[293,906,2219,2259]" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">Geological age. Late Tournaisian.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860F6B29FEFB84ABFCD9F6FA" blockId="29.[241,1227,1878,2682]" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">
Etymology. This species was named after Professor 
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860F6B29FF2B8579FEAFF6AF" box="[243,309,2317,2356]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">I.A.</emphasis>
Talent, Macquarie University as an acknowledgment for his supervision of this work.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860F6B29FEFB851AFB52F5E1" blockId="29.[241,1227,1878,2682]" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">
Remarks. This species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860F6B29FC6D851AFB53F60E" authority="Yoo, 1994" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" box="[949,1225,2414,2453]" class="Gastropoda" family="Elasmonematidae" genus="Kimina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Vetigastropoda" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="globosa" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860F6B29FC6D851AFB53F60E" box="[949,1225,2414,2453]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">Kimina globosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20557BC860F6B29FF2A85E8FEDAF658" box="[242,320,2460,2499]" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in possessing spiral cords, and from 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860F6B29FC1185E8FD90F66A" authority="(Yoo)" baseAuthorityName="Yoo" baseAuthorityYear="1988" class="Gastropoda" family="Murchisoniidae" genus="Pseudoaclisina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="turgida">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860F6B29FC1185E8FEE0F66A" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">Pseudoaclisina turgida</emphasis>
(Yoo)
</taxonomicName>
in having more convex whorls. 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860F6B29FF29858CFDE1F584" authority="Yoo, 1994" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" box="[241,635,2552,2591]" class="Gastropoda" genus="Palaeoalvania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Heterostropha" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="talenti" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860F6B29FF29858CFDE1F584" box="[241,635,2552,2591]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">Palaeoalvania talenti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20557BC860F6B29FD44858CFD70F584" box="[668,746,2552,2591]" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles some Recent rissoids, particularly 
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860F6B29FD4D8652FCB3F5D6" box="[661,809,2598,2637]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860F6B29FD4D8652FCB9F5D6" box="[661,803,2598,2637]" class="Gastropoda" family="Rissoidae" genus="Alvania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Alvania</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
in shell shape and ornament, but differs in having a deviated protoconch.
</paragraph>
